The article discusses the legacy of Martin Luther King Jr. and the importance of his work in applying America's founding ideals to the cause of civil rights. It emphasizes that King believed in the unity of all citizens and the close-knit bonds of the American community. The article also highlights President Donald Trump's efforts to honor King's legacy, such as signing the Martin Luther King, Jr. National Historical Park Act and designating the Martin Luther King, Jr. Federal Holiday. It mentions the bipartisan First Step Act and the promotion of second-chance hiring as steps towards achieving King's dream of equality and justice. The article concludes by stating that the promise of King's dream can be realized by living up to America's shared ideals.